# One of fourteen Arabic letters that do '''not''' affect the pronunciation of the "L" of a preceding definite article. The "L" is the Arabic definite article is pronounced "L" when followed by a moon letter: e.g., {{ARchar|[[القرآن]]}} = al-Qur’an. The fourteen moon letters are:

::{{ARchar|[[أ]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ب]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ج]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ح]]}} , {{ARchar|[[خ]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ع]]}} , {{ARchar|[[غ]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ف]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ق]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ك]]}} , {{ARchar|[[م]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ه]]}} , {{ARchar|[[و]]}} , {{ARchar|[[ى]]}}

:The remainder of the letters are [[sun letter]]s, which do affect the pronunciation of the definite article.

